.TH COHCC 1 "2025-07-16" "Cohesix v1.0" "Cohesix Project"
.SH NAME
cohcc \- Cohesix static compiler wrapper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B cohcc
.RI [ --trace ]
.RI [ --dry-run ]
.IR options ...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B cohcc
is a thin wrapper around \fBclang\fR and \fBrustc\fR used within the Cohesix
sandbox. It enforces static linking and restricts output paths to
\fI/mnt/data\fR. Unsupported options such as \fB-shared\fR or \fB-fPIC\fR are
stripped before invocation. Every run is logged to
\fI/log/cohcc_invocations.log\fR.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --trace
print the final compiler command before execution.
.TP
.B --dry-run
skip execution and only display the command.
.TP
All other arguments are forwarded to the backend compiler after filtering.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /log/cohcc_invocations.log
command history and diagnostics.
.TP
.I /log/cohcc_test_pass.log
automated test result marker.
.SH EXAMPLES
Compile a C program:
.P
.B cohcc hello.c -o /mnt/data/hello
.P
Compile a Rust program:
.P
.B cohcc main.rs -o /mnt/data/hello
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR clang (1),
.BR rustc (1)
